      "text": "3. Velocity pressure, used to calculate external pressures on this floor, shall be qz, where z is set equal to the height above grade of the bottom horizontal surface of the elevated portion of the building plus 25% of the distance from the bottom of the elevated portion of the building to the mean roof height.",
